The Xerox Corporation today reported a 27 percent drop in second-quarter earnings and cited declines in its insurance business.

The company's quarterly profit totaled $130 million, or $1.16 a share, compared with $179 million, or $1.67 a share, in the corresponding quarter a year earlier. Revenue edged up 2.3 percent, to $4.5 billion, from $4.4 billion a year earlier.

Second-quarter revenue from insurance and other financial services was $1.2 billion, down from $1.3 billion a year earlier.

Income from document processing, the company's core business, was $128 million in the second quarter, compared with $123 million in 1989. Revenue increased to $3.3 billion, from $3.1 billion in the second quarter of 1989.